data.title: Southern Connecticut State University Athletics
data.meta_description:
Katrina  Cook (9) F/M  - As a Junior in 2008: 
Played in all 19 games for the Owls, including 17 starts…Closed the year in second on the team in assists
data.text:
As a Junior in 2008:

Played in all 19 games for the Owls, including 17 starts…Closed the year in second on the team in assists (4), tied for third in goals (3) and fourth in total points (10)…Registered a goal and an assist in a 3-0 victory against Queens on 8/31…Tallied an assist at No. 4 C.W. Post on 9/17 and against LeMoyne on 9/23…Notched a goal in a 3-1 victory at Stonehill on 10/15…Found the back of the net in a 3-0 victory against AIC on 10/21…Assisted the go-ahead goal in the Northeast-10 Conference Tournament semifinals at No. 20 Franklin Pierce on 11/6.

As a Sophomore in 2007:

Played in 17 games for the Owls…Made 16 starts…Scored a goal at Post on 9/5…Scored a goal against Bentley on 9/8…Named to the Northeast-10 Weekly Honor Roll for the week ending on 9/9…Scored a goal at American International on 9/29…Scored the game-winning goal against Southern New Hampshire on 10/3.

As a Freshman in 2006:

Played in three games for the Owls…Made two starts…Did not register a point.

Before Southern Connecticut State University:

Two-time All-Area pick at Minisink Valley (N.Y.) High School…Also participated in softball, basketball and track and field.

Personal:

The daughter of Mary and Raymond Cook…Born in Brooklyn, N.Y…An exercise science major.
